        <div> <h3> Causes & Corrections </h3> </div>
        <div class="text-div">
          <p> Asymmetrical neck pain is a result of <b>repeated stress</b> and happens when you habitually favor the use of one side of the body over the other. 
              At work, this is often caused by sitting with the <i>head tilted/turned to one side</i> for long periods of time. </p>
        </div>
        <div class="image-row">
          <img class="short" src="images/neck/phone-to-ear.png">
          <img class="short" src="images/neck/purse-asym.jpeg">
          {{!-- <img class="long" src="images/neck/how-healthy-is-your-handbag.jpg"> --}}
          <img class="short" src="images/neck/asym-sleep.png">
        </div>
        <div class="text-div">
          <p> This can also be caused by factors like the tendency to wear single-strap bags (purses, messenger bags, backpacks, etc.) or the preference for a particular side while sleeping. </p>
           {{!-- <p> If the strain is located on the same side as your "mouse arm", this may be related to the way you are holding your mouse (refer to the <a href="/shoulders">"Shoulders"</a> section).</p> --}}
